The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 May is 42,125 (4,875.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 May, there were 53 new confirmed cases (6.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 May, there were 98 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 46% (45 fewer cases).
